      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To ensure a 100% pass rate despite flaky components, I recommend implementing robust explicit waits within your Playwright tests instead of relying solely on implicit timeouts. Specifically, use `await page.waitForSelector()` with a reasonable timeout for critical elements like the login form and visualization containers. Furthermore, introduce retry logic around the entire test suite execution in your CI/CD configuration, which will automatically re-run failed tests a few times before declaring a definitive failure. This combination minimizes timing-related failures while providing a safety net for transient backend issues.",
